<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-brP5LWGuK5A/WJoMoMtaXeI/AAAAAAAALnE/V-dFaNpdQeEiW10BXYhlL6xSAUJoE7_pACLcB/s1600/AP2070047.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="406" src="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-brP5LWGuK5A/WJoMoMtaXeI/AAAAAAAALnE/V-dFaNpdQeEiW10BXYhlL6xSAUJoE7_pACLcB/s640/AP2070047.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-zd5YeHjRJKU/WJoMo8RFkxI/AAAAAAAALnI/WHg1n9SLJ70UnfijmDIBXcdsuFIPuXY8ACLcB/s1600/AP2070043.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="442" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-zd5YeHjRJKU/WJoMo8RFkxI/AAAAAAAALnI/WHg1n9SLJ70UnfijmDIBXcdsuFIPuXY8ACLcB/s640/AP2070043.jpg" width="640" /></a></div>Lighter winds for the <a href="http://www.expeditionguide.com/winterskills.php">Winter Skills Course</a> today giving us much more options of where to go. Choosing to use mechanical assistance we used the White Corries chairlift to take us up onto the slopes of <i>Meall a Bhuiridh</i>. Even with the much improved weather it was still a case of seeing just what opportunities the mountain offered us in ticking through the course syllabus.&nbsp; Even sticking as best as we could to the exposed rocks the going was still labored in the soft snow. We were able to run through some of the ice axe drills and managed to fashion a crampon piste by scrapping out a square of firm snow. The drifts were good for digging an emergency shelter, we reached our first Munro summit of the week and we still had time for a quick blast on the ski area sledges.<br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-xW02RhxmEc4/WJoMrOAtHFI/AAAAAAAALnM/0465OZn_bOMb4nMtXEpRyim3lpPL3r9JgCLcB/s1600/AP2070060.jpg" imageanchor="1" styl